Program: Omnibus
Title: Mind Games
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mcg
Last Broadcast Date: 06 February 2002
The little known story of the emotions and personal relationships of the politicians who brought about the end of communism in Europe between 1989-1991. Contributors include James Baker, Hungarian PM Miklós Németh, Douglas Hurd and psychotherapist Gabrielle Rifkind.